# Phase 43: Dashboard Polish & Crypto Off-Ramp Docs

This implementation plan covers the user's request to improve the Creator Studio Dashboard, add dynamic fiat conversion logic for Solana, and provide a legal off-ramp guide in the Help Center.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Dashboard Mobile Polish & Crypto Price Conversion
#### [MODIFY] [DashboardClient.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/studio/dashboard/DashboardClient.tsx)
-   **SOL to USDC Conversion**: 
    -   I'll add a static conversion mock (e.g., 1 SOL = $180 USDC) to calculate the fiat equivalent of the user's total Solana native earnings.
    -   This value will be displayed within the `trend` token of the [StatCard](file:///C:/GOLive/app/studio/dashboard/DashboardClient.tsx#553-575) as `≈ $X.XX USDC` so it appears naturally next to the `X.XX SOL` balance.
-   **Mobile Responsiveness**: 
    -   Update the main Tab Navigation (`Channel Content` / `Analytics & Revenue`) container with `w-full overflow-x-auto whitespace-nowrap md:w-auto` to prevent layout breaks on small screens.
    -   Ensure transaction and content managers maintain native horizontal scroll momentum (`overflow-x-auto`) for dense tabular data on mobile.

### 2. Help Center: Legal Off-Ramp Guide
#### [MODIFY] [Help Page](file:///C:/GOLive/app/help/page.tsx)
-   **New FAQ Category**: Add a dedicated `Crypto & Off-Ramping` bento card and topic section.
-   **Content**: 
    -   Include guides on transferring crypto to centralized exchanges (CEXs like Coinbase or Kraken) for legal fiat withdrawal.
    -   Include a high-level disclaimer regarding tax implications for creator earnings, advising users to maintain clear records and consult professionals.

